Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.65,0:14:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The heck is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.24,0:14:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, S-Sayu said that was for {replace}Lord Uroko{Uroko-sama}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.10,0:14:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For goodness' sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.44,0:14:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you thought \Nyou'd catch me with {\i1}that{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.58,0:14:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems you don't think much of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}Lord Uroko{Uroko-sama}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.22,0:14:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell Mukaido's granddaughter—Manaka, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.70,0:14:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell her that she's got nothing on that old bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.33,0:14:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The heck are you doing up here on the surface?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.86,0:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my duty to watch over the people of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.63,0:14:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as nearly everyone's asleep right now, I got rather bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.36,0:14:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've been keeping an eye on us ever since we woke up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.23,0:14:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you come out sooner, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.12,0:14:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a scale of the sea god.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.88,0:14:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't manifest as freely \Non the surface as in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.68,0:15:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.71,0:15:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What a wonderful scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Smells like you're ovulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.01,0:15:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.96,0:15:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe I didn't notice it the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.12,0:15:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and your Ena has \Ndeveloped quite nicely, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.60,0:15:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It has?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.48,0:15:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out, you scaly pervert!{Somehow way better than "perverted scale"...}{on a scale from 1 to 10, how perverted is he?}{11!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.06,0:15:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.99,0:15:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren't you looking for me all this time \Nbecause you had something to ask me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.21,0:15:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I nearly forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.16,0:15:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}Lord Uroko{Uroko-sama}, what's happening to the surface?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.83,0:15:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it gonna keep getting worse up here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.66,0:15:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about everyone in Shishio?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.80,0:15:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when are they gonna wake up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure there's nothing else you want to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.15,0:15:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to Manaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.92,0:16:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Can she never go back to the sea now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.71,0:16:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And to top it off, she's forgotten so much from before she fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what the hell is happening to her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.82,0:16:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Manaka had become the Wooden Maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.15,0:16:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wooden Maiden?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.70,0:16:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The maiden sacrificed to the sea god \Nwho later bore his child...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.44,0:16:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She left someone she loved on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When she fell into depression
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.38,0:16:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because she couldn't let go of those feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.39,0:16:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the sea god saw that and \Nreturned her to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.03,0:16:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But he took something in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.62,0:16:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that story already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.95,0:16:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea god took her Ena in return, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.46,0:16:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that got to do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.23,0:16:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That maiden returned to the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.16,0:16:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and many years passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.85,0:16:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea god lost his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.22,0:17:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and his body dissolved into the sea, \Nbecoming one with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.93,0:17:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I am one of the scales that fell off \Nwhen that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.09,0:17:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day, fragments of the sea god's emotions still drift through the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.44,0:17:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fragments of his emotions?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.50,0:17:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither good nor evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.75,0:17:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Rage, sadness, happiness, envy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.40,0:17:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All of his raw emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.99,0:17:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit fire is also a part of him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.80,0:17:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's a bit more structured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.70,0:17:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... I suppose you could call it his consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.57,0:17:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit fire wishes to prevent what is about to befall the sea and the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.51,0:17:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the fragments of his \Nemotions that remain in the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.52,0:17:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,sense the encroachment \Nof human civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this, they sometimes imbue the dangers of the sea with semi-sentient purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.43,0:17:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,On the day of the Boatdrift Ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.43,0:18:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,those emotions dragged Manaka to the \Nbottom of the sea and made her the sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.41,0:18:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems the yearning the sea god felt for the sacrificial maiden was among those fragments.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the graveyard \Nof Wooden Maidens,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.14,0:18:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Manaka was covered in a sheet of thick Ena, \Nand she became the sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to her, the sea became calmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.94,0:18:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and the impending demise \Nof the surface was halted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.24,0:18:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the spirit fire and the fragments of emotions became one,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.90,0:18:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and an equilibrium was reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.23,0:18:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.85,0:18:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Manaka could not let go of her feelings and fully accept her fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.76,0:18:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so those feelings tried to free her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.30,0:18:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Her feelings began destroying her Ena and sending bits of it toward the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.27,0:18:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which in turn created a small current.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.07,0:18:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the current that led us \Nto Shioshishio, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.27,0:19:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The tiny flakes of Manaka's Ena collided in this current and made a distinctive sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.37,0:19:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That was what the girl from the surface heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.72,0:19:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, that day{what I heard}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound I heard was Manaka{-san}'s Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.05,0:19:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.78,0:19:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Manaka{-san}'s emotions!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.15,0:19:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are Miuna and Hikari{-kun}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.76,0:19:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You think something happened to them{they're okay}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not little kids anymore, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.18,0:19:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure there's no reason to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.79,0:19:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When you began your search for Manaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.24,0:19:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the sea god's {fragments of }emotions feared the \NWooden Maiden would be taken away,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.95,0:19:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so they decided to take \Nsomething {\i1}else{\i0} away from Manaka{, just as they had done before}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Namaka, rawr!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.15,0:20:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the moment Manaka lost the rest of her Ena all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Rawr!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.99,0:20:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When Manaka became the sacrifice, the sea became calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.59,0:20:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But now that it's lost her, the demise of the surface may arrive sooner than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.04,0:20:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.07,0:20:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean to tell me that \Nthe surface is all messed up
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.86,0:20:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because we rescued Manaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.15,0:20:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying it would've been better if Manaka had stayed asleep down there forever?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.38,0:20:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.60,0:20:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is that supposed to mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.70,0:20:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it may arrive {\i1}sooner{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.72,0:20:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It will still be long after you die,\N{comma for dramatic emphasis} and long after your children die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.23,0:20:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.81,0:20:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you said that they took something else and {that }that's{[sic]} when she lost the rest of her Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.25,0:20:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean that what they took from Manaka{-san} wasn't just her Ena?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.61,0:20:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just her Ena?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.26,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikari, you are in love with \NManaka, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.86,0:20:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell does {\i1}that{\i0} have to do with anything right now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Your feelings for Manaka may never reach her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.64,0:21:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's possible that no one's ever will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.62,0:21:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.21,0:21:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikari?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What they took from Manaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.81,0:21:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.47,0:21:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Rawr! Boom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.50,0:21:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.71,0:21:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,her ability to fall in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah? Then take {\i1}this{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.23,0:21:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.83,0:21:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.29,0:21:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Manaka is now unable to \Nfall in love with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.80,0:21:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Oh no! You got me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.62,0:21:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, welcome home,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.26,0:21:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Miuna{-chan}, Hii{-kun}!
